SIMPLE: congener
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congener
<hw>Con"ge*ner</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>congener</ets>. See <er>Congenerous</er>.]</ety> <def>A thing of
the same genus, species, or kind; a thing allied in nature, character,
or action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cherry tree has been often grafted on the laurel, to which it
is a <qex>congener</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>P. Miller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our elk is more polygamous in his habits than any other deer
except his <qex>congener</qex>, the red deer of Europe.</q>
<rj><qau>Caton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congeneracy</ent>⟦br⟧
